- **Rheumatoid Drug Type:** The global arthritis market is segmented by rheumatoid drug type into biologics, non-biologics, steroids, analgesics, glucocorticoids, and others. Biologics are increasingly utilized in the treatment of rheumatoid arthritis due to their targeted approach in modulating the immune system. Non-biologic drugs, such as methotrexate, are commonly prescribed as a first-line therapy. Steroids provide rapid relief of inflammation but are typically used for short-term management. Analgesics help alleviate pain associated with arthritis, while glucocorticoids offer potent anti-inflammatory effects.

- **Rheumatoid Treatment:** The rheumatoid treatment segment encompasses a range of interventions, including synovectomy, tendon repair, joint fusion, symptomatic treatment, intermediate corticosteroid therapies, and disease-modifying antirheumatic drug (DMARD) therapies. Synovectomy involves the surgical removal of the inflamed synovial membrane in the joints. Tendon repair aims to restore function in damaged tendons. Joint fusion may be performed to stabilize joints and reduce pain. Symptomatic treatment focuses on managing pain and inflammation. DMARD therapies target the underlying immune dysfunction in rheumatoid arthritis.

